<figure xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="fig_3"><head>Figure 3 .</head><label>3</label><figDesc>Figure 3. [Left panel]: Torque density as a function of separation from planet (r − rp)/Hp in full 3D. Vertical dashed lines mark all the locations of the sign change of the torque. The torque density is defined as an amount of angular momentum deposited to the disk, so it is mostly positive for r &gt; rp and mostly negative for r &lt; rp. [Right panel]: Absolute value of the torque density from global 3D simulations (black lines) in comparison with 2D shearing sheet calculations (Petrovich &amp; Rafikov 2012; Rafikov &amp; Petrovich 2012) (red line), and linear theory Goldreich &amp; Tremaine (1980) (blue dashed line). The solid (dashed) black line corresponds to r &gt; rp (r &lt; rp).</figDesc></figure>
